Glasgow man, 23, dies during Turkey holidayA YOUNG man from Glasgow has died after an accident in Turkey.The 23-year-old is thought to have been been on holiday with friends.He is believed to have been killed during a road crash in Fethiye on Monday.The death was confirmed by the Foreign and Commonwealth Office.Another person remains in hospital following the incident.An FCO spokesman said: &quot;We can confirm the death of a British national in Fethiye, Turkey, on June 22 and the hospitalisation of a second British national involved in the same incident.&quot;We are providing consular assistance.&quot;